<title>USA: Sparks sees 1997/98 cotton crop at 17.6 mln bales.</title>
<headline>Sparks sees 1997/98 cotton crop at 17.6 mln bales.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1997-08-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Memphis-based analytical firm Sparks Companies estimated 1997/98 U.S. cotton production at 17.642 million bales, trade sources said.</p>
<p>The U.S. Department of Agriculture in July projected the 1997/98 (Aug 1-July 31) crop at 18 million bales.</p>
<p>USDA also projected the national average yield at 670 lbs per harvested acre, above the Sparks projection of 644 lbs.</p>
<p>A spokesman from Sparks declined to comment on the estimates.</p>
<p>((Doris Frankel 312-983-7305))</p>
